gomodel:SYNGO_3830  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"Effect of Parkin dysfunction on Syt11 accumulation\"\n- \"Furthermore, the parkin-mediated decrease of Syt11 level was prevented by 12-h pretreatment with the proteasome inhibitor MG132 (Fig. 1d), confirming that parkin-mediated Syt11 degradation occurs through the proteasome pathway.\"\n[Fig.5: \"Syt11 inhibits vesicle pool replenishment in dopaminergic neurons\"]\nFig.7: \"Syt11 knockdown rescues parkin knockdown-induced deficits in DA release and motor behavior.\"\nFig.8: \"Expression of Syt11 in dopaminergic neurons is critical for parkin to mediate DA release and motor deficits.\"\n\nNote: Syt11 is a known regulator of dopamine SV endocytosis.. Experimental description: - \"Mice were housed in the animal facility with a maximum of five mice per cage ...\"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2018-06-29" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_3830" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

